S4: exploration of the rt and rt.var trajectories

I. S. Plank

2025-05-14

S4.1 Introduction

This R Markdown script analyses data from the PAL (probabilistic associative learning) task of the EMBA project. HGF parameters were extrated based on the subject-specific reaction times beforehand in MATLAB.

Package versions

The following packages are used in this RMarkdown file:

## [1] "R version 4.5.0 (2025-04-11)"
## [1] "knitr version 1.50"
## [1] "ggplot2 version 3.5.2"
## [1] "tidyverse version 2.0.0"
## [1] "ggpubr version 0.6.0"
## [1] "ggrain version 0.0.4"
## [1] "BayesFactor version 0.9.12.4.7"

Preparation

First, we load the parameters from the winning model.

# load the data
df = read_csv(file.path("data", "PAL_data.csv"))

# length of blocks
nblock = 24

Reaction times

df %>%
  mutate(
    rt.cor = if_else(acc, rt, NA)
  ) %>%
  group_by(diagnosis, trl) %>%
  summarise(
    rt.std = sd(rt.cor, na.rm = T)/sqrt(n()),
    rt.avg = mean(rt.cor, na.rm = T)
  ) %>%
  ggplot(., aes(group = diagnosis, x = trl)) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = rt.avg - rt.std, ymax = rt.avg + rt.std, fill = diagnosis), 
              alpha = 0.25) + 
  geom_line(aes(colour = diagnosis, y = rt.avg)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = c(72, 264), colour = "black") + 
  labs(title = "RTs across task", x = "trials", y = "RT (ms)") +
  scale_fill_manual(values  = custom.col4) +
  scale_color_manual(values = custom.col4) +
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(legend.position = "bottom", plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), 
        legend.direction = "horizontal", text = element_text(size = 15))

df %>%
  mutate(
    rt.cor = if_else(acc, rt, NA),
    block = if_else(trl%%nblock == 0,trl/nblock,NA)
  ) %>%
  fill(block, .direction = "up") %>%
  group_by(subID, diagnosis, block) %>%
  summarise(
    rt.avg = mean(rt.cor, na.rm = T)
  ) %>%
  group_by(diagnosis, block) %>%
  summarise(
    rt.se  = sd(rt.avg, na.rm = T)/sqrt(n()),
    rt.avg = mean(rt.avg, na.rm = T)
  ) %>%
  ggplot(., aes(x = block, group = diagnosis)) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = rt.avg - rt.se, ymax = rt.avg + rt.se, fill = diagnosis), 
              alpha = 0.25) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = rt.avg, colour = diagnosis)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = c(72/nblock, 264/nblock), colour = "black") + 
  labs(title = "RTs across task", x = sprintf("block of %d trials", nblock), 
       y = "mean RT (ms)") +
  scale_fill_manual(values  = custom.col4) +
  scale_color_manual(values = custom.col4) +
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(legend.position = "bottom", plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), 
        legend.direction = "horizontal", text = element_text(size = 15))

Reaction time variance

df %>%
  mutate(
    rt.cor = if_else(acc, rt, NA),
    block = if_else(trl%%nblock == 0,trl/nblock,NA)
  ) %>%
  fill(block, .direction = "up") %>%
  group_by(subID, diagnosis, block) %>%
  summarise(
    rt.var = sd(rt.cor, na.rm = T)
  ) %>%
  group_by(diagnosis, block) %>%
  summarise(
    rt.se  = sd(rt.var, na.rm = T)/sqrt(n()),
    rt.var = mean(rt.var, na.rm = T)
  ) %>%
  ggplot(., aes(x = block, group = diagnosis)) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = rt.var - rt.se, ymax = rt.var + rt.se, fill = diagnosis), 
              alpha = 0.25) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = rt.var, colour = diagnosis)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = c(72/nblock, 264/nblock), colour = "black") + 
  labs(title = "RT vars across task", x = sprintf("block of %d trials", nblock), 
       y = "standard deviation RT (ms)") +
  scale_fill_manual(values  = custom.col4) +
  scale_color_manual(values = custom.col4) +
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(legend.position = "bottom", plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), 
        legend.direction = "horizontal", text = element_text(size = 15))
